  "prompt": "Can I get into the CSE in VIT Chennai at 70+ marks?",
  "response": "Getting into the Computer Science and Engineering (CSE) program at VIT Chennai with 70+ marks will depend on several factors, including the specific entrance exam you are referring to and the cut-off marks for that particular year.\n\n1. **VITEEE Exam:** If you are referring to the VIT Engineering Entrance Examination (VITEEE), admission to VIT Chennai is primarily determined by your rank in this exam rather than just your marks. The ranks for CSE tend to be competitive due to high demand.\n\n2. **Cut-off Ranks:** These can vary each year based on the number of applicants, difficulty of the exam, and overall performance of the candidates. Generally, CSE is one of the most sought-after courses, and it typically requires a high rank.\n\n3. **Campus Preference:** VIT Vellore is generally more competitive compared to VIT Chennai, so the required rank for admission in VIT Vellore might be higher than for VIT Chennai.\n\n4. **Counseling Process:** Admission will also depend on how you perform in the counseling process, during which you can express your campus and course preferences.\n\nTo get the most accurate and updated information, you should check the official VIT website or contact the admissions office. They can provide specific details about required ranks and the admission process for the current year.",
